    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-05T19:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-05T19:36:00-05:00" n="911"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d911">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2740.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-05T18:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 5, 1912—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Torreón situation better. Danger of complications at Ciudad Juárez appears to
                    have passed for the moment. Situation in Chihuahua very bad; State government
                    apparently helpless and governor has resigned. Orozco will be made military
                    dictator if he remains faithful; he has the President’s entire confidence. Much
                    brigandage and lawlessness in Durango with prospects of an organized outbreak at
                    any time. No improvement in southern Mexico. There is some excitement here on
                    account of sensational press dispatches from the United States announcing
                    prospective intervention. At the celebration of constitution day to-day an
                    enormous crowd was present but the President was received without any
                    demonstration and in silence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
